{"_id": "NDlhYTZiNDk3ZDU2", "name": "Help: UniversalVTTImporter", "permission": {"default": 0}, "folder": null, "flags": {"R20Converter": {"handout-order": 13, "handout-archived": true}}, "sort": 130000, "entryTime": 0, "content": "<div style=\"font-weight: bold; border-bottom: 1px solid black;font-size: 130%;\">UniversalVTTImporter v0.1.12</div> <div style=\"padding-left:10px;margin-bottom:3px;\"><p>UniversalVTTImporter provides a way to setup Dynamic Lighting lines and Lights stored in Universal VTT format, ala Dungeondraft.</p></div> <b>Commands</b> <div style=\"padding-left: 10px;padding-right:20px\"><b><span style=\"font-family:serif;\">!uvtt &#91;--help &#124; --clear &#124; --no-objects&#93;</span></b> <ul><li><b>--help</b> -- Displays this help and configuration options.</li><li><b>--clear</b> -- Removes all imported content for the selected graphics.</li><li><b>--no-objects</b> -- Skips creating lines for Opaque Objects.</li></ul></div> <b>Import Process</b><div style=\"padding-left: 10px;padding-right:20px\"><p>The process for importing is pretty straight forward, but there are several steps, as follows:</p> <ol><li>From your Universal VTT supporting mapping program, such as Dungeondraft, export your map as a <code>.png</code> or <code>.jpg</code> file.  The API cannot create images from the Universal VTT, so you will need to upload it manually.</li><li>Next export the Universal VTT version into a <code>.dd2vtt</code> file.</li><li>Drop your map image file onto a page and scale it as desired.</li><li>Open the properties by double clicking the image.</li><li>Load the Universal VTT file in a text editor and copy the contents.  You can use the <a href=\"http://roll20api.net/uvtti.html\">Universal VTT Import Sanitizer</a> do this efficiently.</li><li>Paste the contents into the GM Notes section of the map graphic and save changes.</li><li>With the graphic selected, run <code>!uvtt</code></li></ol> <p>Your map should now have dynamic lighting lines, lines for doors and windows, and light sources from the original.</p></div> ", "img": "modules/alteria/journal/013_-_Help_3A_UniversalVTTImporter/avatar.png"}